<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/5617: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-03T14:00:00-04:00">June 3, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 2, 8 p.m. We shall appreciate whatever information you may be
                            able informally and discreetly to obtain as to the number, identity, and
                            present circumstances of the Americans reported to have been aboard the
                                <hi rend="italic">City of Barcelona</hi>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>